# Commit message template using Conventional Commits
# Format: <type>(<optional scope>): <description>
#
# Examples:
#   feat: add login endpoint
#   fix(auth): reject expired JWTs
#   chore(deps): bump goreleaser to v1.20.0
#   docs(readme): add usage examples
#   refactor(parser): simplify error handling
#   test(config): add unit test for invalid input
#
# Allowed types:
#   feat     – new feature
#   fix      – bug fix
#   docs     – documentation change
#   style    – code style (formatting, etc.)
#   refactor – refactor (not adding features or fixing bugs)
#   perf     – performance improvement
#   test     – adding or updating tests
#   chore    – maintenance (e.g. build scripts, tooling)
